        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 28 at 5:10PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 510 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles east of Mandeville, or 8 miles east of Texarkana, moving north
at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Texarkana, Hope, Fulton, Mandeville, Genoa, McNab, Homan, Hervey,
Red Bluff and Millwood.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
